CSS provides multiple ways to specify colors for text, backgrounds, borders, and other elements.

**Named Colors:**
CSS has 140 named colors.
```css
h1 {
  color: red;
}
p {
  color: blue;
}
```

**HEX Colors:**
Hexadecimal color notation (#RRGGBB).
```css
p {
  color: #ff0000; /* red */
  color: #00ff00; /* green */
  color: #0000ff; /* blue */
}
```

**RGB Colors:**
Red, Green, Blue values (0-255).
```css
p {
  color: rgb(255, 0, 0); /* red */
  color: rgb(0, 255, 0); /* green */
  color: rgb(0, 0, 255); /* blue */
}
```

**RGBA Colors (with transparency):**
```css
p {
  color: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5); /* 50% transparent red */
}
```

**HSL Colors:**
Hue, Saturation, Lightness.
```css
p {
  color: hsl(0, 100%, 50%); /* red */
  color: hsl(120, 100%, 50%); /* green */
  color: hsl(240, 100%, 50%); /* blue */
}
```

**HSLA Colors (with transparency):**
```css
p {
  color: hsla(0, 100%, 50%, 0.5);
}
```

**Common Color Properties:**
- `color` - Text color
- `background-color` - Element background
- `border-color` - Border color

The background-color property sets the background color of an element.

**Basic Usage:**
```css
body {
  background-color: lightblue;
}

div {
  background-color: #ff0000;
}
```

**With Text Color:**
```css
h1 {
  background-color: black;
  color: white;
}
```

**Transparency:**
```css
div {
  background-color: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.3);
}
```

**Best Practices:**
- Ensure good contrast between text and background
- Use lighter backgrounds with dark text
- Use darker backgrounds with light text
- Test color combinations for accessibility

The background-image property sets an image as the background of an element.

**Basic Usage:**
```css
body {
  background-image: url('paper.gif');
}
```

**Multiple Backgrounds:**
```css
body {
  background-image: url('bg1.png'), url('bg2.png');
}
```

**Background Repeat:**
Controls how the image repeats.
```css
body {
  background-image: url('gradient.png');
  background-repeat: repeat-x; /* repeat horizontally */
  background-repeat: repeat-y; /* repeat vertically */
  background-repeat: no-repeat; /* don't repeat */
}
```

**Background Position:**
Sets the starting position of the background image.
```css
body {
  background-image: url('img_tree.png');
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-position: right top;
}
```

**Common Positions:**
- `left top`, `left center`, `left bottom`
- `center top`, `center center`, `center bottom`
- `right top`, `right center`, `right bottom`
- `x% y%` - Percentage positions
- `xpos ypos` - Pixel positions

CSS borders allow you to add decorative borders around elements.

**Border Style:**
Required property for borders to show.
```css
p {
  border-style: solid;
}
```

**Border Styles:**
- `dotted` - Dotted border
- `dashed` - Dashed border
- `solid` - Solid border
- `double` - Double border
- `groove` - 3D grooved border
- `ridge` - 3D ridged border
- `inset` - 3D inset border
- `outset` - 3D outset border
- `none` - No border
- `hidden` - Hidden border

**Border Width:**
```css
p {
  border-style: solid;
  border-width: 5px;
}
```

**Border Color:**
```css
p {
  border-style: solid;
  border-color: red;
}
```

**Border Shorthand:**
```css
p {
  border: 5px solid red;
}
```

**Individual Sides:**
```css
p {
  border-top: 5px solid red;
  border-right: 5px solid blue;
  border-bottom: 5px solid green;
  border-left: 5px solid yellow;
}

The border-radius property rounds the corners of an element.

**Basic Usage:**
```css
div {
  border: 2px solid red;
  border-radius: 10px;
}
```

**Circular Elements:**
```css
div {
  border-radius: 50%; /* makes element circular */
}
```

**Individual Corners:**
```css
div {
  border-radius: 15px 50px 30px 5px;
  /* top-left, top-right, bottom-right, bottom-left */
}
```

**Shorthand:**
```css
div {
  border-radius: 15px 50px; /* top-left/bottom-right, top-right/bottom-left */
}
```

**Elliptical Corners:**
```css
div {
  border-radius: 50px / 15px; /* horizontal radius / vertical radius */
}
```

**Common Uses:**
- Creating circular profile images
- Making card components with rounded corners
- Creating buttons with rounded edges
- Designing modern UI elements
